                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Initialization",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure begins by setting "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "NOCOUNT ON",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to prevent the sending of DONE_IN_PROC messages, which can improve performance by reducing network traffic. It also sets the transaction isolation level to READ UNCOMMITTED, allowing the procedure to read uncommitted changes from other transactions, which can reduce locking contention but results in reading dirty data."
                }
